%U A116160 669421494,702338994,715976338,750005718,960645294,999999994
%N A116160 Numbers k such that k concatenated with itself gives the product of two numbers which differ by 7.
%C A116160 If k has d digits, the concatenation is k//k = 10^d*k+k = m*(m+7), therefore k//k-8 = 10^d*k+k-8 = (m-1)*(m+8), so there is a large overlap with A116109. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 22 2026
%Y A116160 Cf. A020338, A116152, A116159, A116161, A116167, A116291.
